ions-images/tim-morabito/ID-100221203-1adab6e7e5e8a4f49457272b5feac1a1.jpg 1x"/></span></span>\n	</div>\n	<div class="cn-table-cell cn-team-member-name">\n		<span class="fn n notranslate"> <span class="given-name">Tim</span> <span class="additional-name">C</span> <span class="family-name">Morabito</span> </span>\n					<span class="title notranslate">Placement Specialist</span>\n			</div>\n\n	\n	\n\n			<div class="cn-table-cell cn-team-member-email">\n			<span class="email-address-block">\n	<span class="email cn-email-address cn-preferred cn-email-address-preferred"><span class="email-address"><span class="qrpelcg"><n pynff="inyhr" gvgyr="Gvz Zbenovgb jbex rznvy." uers="znvygb:GvzPZbenovgb@rvaebg.pbz">GvzPZbenovgb@rvaebg.pbz</n></span><noscript><span style="unicode-bidi: bidi-override; direction:rtl;">mo&#99;.to&#114;&#110;&#105;e&#64;o&#116;&#105;&#98;aro&#77;&#67;miT</span></noscript></span><span class="type" style="display: none;">INTERNET</span></span>\n</span>\n		</div>\n	\n\n	\n</div>\n</div>\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/introducing-the-team-block/">Introducing the Team Block</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/oI94aA-zGO0" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"https://connections-pro.com/introducing-the-team-block/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"2";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:55:"https://connections-pro.com/introducing-the-team-block/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:1;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:64:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"2019 Roadmap";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/A0uLsJb8YS8/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"https://connections-pro.com/2019-roadmap/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 12 Mar 2019 21:13:06 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Development Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"https://connections-pro.com/?p=486773";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:495:"<p>Over the past few months a lot of work has been put in to support the new Block editor (Gutenberg) in WordPress 5. This was a really challenging exercise, but one I feel was well worth the effort. Both the Directory and the Upcoming List blocks, for the most part, have feature parity with their ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/2019-roadmap/">2019 Roadmap</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1909:"\n<p>Over the past few months a lot of work has been put in to support the new Block editor (Gutenberg) in WordPress 5. This was a really challenging exercise, but one I feel was well worth the effort. Both the Directory and the Upcoming List blocks, for the most part, have feature parity with their shortcode equivalents. There are even a few features the blocks have which do not exist in the shortcodes!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So with that complete, what&#8217;s next?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several main goals for this year:</p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Update the Social Network icons. The existing icon set is getting pretty dated.</li><li>Add a new Team block. This will be a highly customizable block providing you many design options which will allow you to build team pages using the data from your directory. Similar premium plugins sell for $20 and more. We&#8217;re bringing this to you as a free feature!</li><li>Add a Map block. Well, actually two. The first will be a simple generic map block, like many of the others available for the new Editor. It&#8217;ll allow you to add a map with an address pin to a page. The purpose of this block will be primarily to help flesh out the new Mapping  API built into Connections at the end of last year (did you notice the switch ;) ). The second map block will  be to pull in addresses from the directory data and add them as pins with popups. This block will be great to use as a basic store locator.</li><li>Move from microdata to Schema.org for even better SEO.</li><li>And lastly, more of a developer focused feature, continue to build out the WordPress REST API support.</li></ol>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/2019-roadmap/">2019 Roadmap</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/A0uLsJb8YS8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:46:"https://connections-pro.com/2019-roadmap/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"https://connections-pro.com/2019-roadmap/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WordPress 5.1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/viH7lmRdXHk/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-1/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 20 Feb 2019 18:22:33 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Announcement";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Development Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"https://connections-pro.com/?p=485227";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:557:"<p>We wrote previously, when WordPress 5.0 was released in December, suggesting to to hold off on upgrading due to concerns over known issues. Since then WordPress has released a few minor updates which addressed the bigger concerns. With the release of WordPress 5.1 is emanate, we can wholeheartedly recommend upgrading. Connections is fully compatible and ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-1/">WordPress 5.1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1803:"<p><img class="alignright size-full wp-image-479219" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/block-directory.png" alt="" width="279" height="279" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/block-directory.png 279w, https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/block-directory-150x150.png 150w, https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/block-directory-250x250.png 250w, https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/block-directory-128x128.png 128w, https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/block-directory-256x256.png 256w" sizes="(max-width: 279px) 100vw, 279px" />We wrote previously, when WordPress 5.0 was released in December, suggesting to to hold off on upgrading due to concerns over known issues. Since then WordPress has released a few minor updates which addressed the bigger concerns. With the release of WordPress 5.1 is emanate, we can wholeheartedly recommend upgrading. Connections is fully compatible and has been ready to go since December.</p>\n<p>We have been hard at work making sure Connections works great with WordPress 5. We&#8217;ve added two new block, the <a href="/documentation/block/directory/">Directory block</a> and the <a href="/documentation/block/upcoming-list/">Upcoming block</a>, which can easily replace the old shortcodes. In fact, if you are using the new WordPress Block editor, we recommend using these blocks instead of the legacy shortcode. We have more blocks in the works which we are looking forward to releasing.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-1/">WordPress 5.1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/viH7lmRdXHk" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-1/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-1/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:70:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Update Announcement: Link 4.0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/-PsELW0uxwE/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-4-0/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Fri, 28 Dec 2018 16:04:05 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Announcement";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Development Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Pro Module";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"https://connections-pro.com/?p=480311";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:536:"<p>A major update to Link has been released adding these highly requested features: Bulk link your existing WP Users to your existing Connections Entries. Link a WP User when you add or edit a Connections Entry. This smart new feature will auto suggest WP Users as you type making it quick and easy to find ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-4-0/">Update Announcement: Link 4.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1864:"<p><a href="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/link-suggest-a-user.png"><img width="220" height="157" alt="" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/480323_link-suggest-a-user-220x157.png" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/480323_link-suggest-a-user-220x157@2x.png 2x"  /></a><a href="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/link-entry-status.png"><img width="220" height="34" alt="" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/480322_link-entry-status-220x34.png" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/480322_link-entry-status-220x34@2x.png 2x"  /></a></p>\n<div class="clear"></div>\n<p>A major update to Link has been released adding these highly requested features:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bulk link your existing WP Users to your existing Connections Entries.</li>\n<li>Link a WP User when you add or edit a Connections Entry. This smart new feature will auto suggest WP Users as you type making it quick and easy to find the WP User that you want to link the Entry to.</li>\n<li>Improved feedback on the Managed admin page so you can quickly see which entries have been linked and to which WP User the Entry has been linked to.</li>\n<li>New Entry action link to allow you to instantly jump to the linked WP Users profile page.</li>\n<li>You can now quickly unlink a WP User from an Entry.</li>\n<li>Lastly, there is now a tool which can be used to bulk unlink all WP Users from the Entries.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-4-0/">Update Announcement: Link 4.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/-PsELW0uxwE" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-4-0/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-4-0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:67:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"WordPress 5.0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/rZjqCMwYa1M/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-0/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 06 Dec 2018 16:43:08 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Announcement";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Development Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:37:"https://connections-pro.com/?p=478280";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:525:"<p>WordPress 5.0 is due to be released shortly unless there is a last minute decision to delay the release. If you are here reading this, then you are likely asking yourself if Connections is compatible. The short answer is yes! During the past month Connections has been tested against the beta and release candidate versions ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-0/">WordPress 5.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1058:"<p>WordPress 5.0 is due to be released shortly unless there is a last minute decision to delay the release. If you are here reading this, then you are likely asking yourself if Connections is compatible. The short answer is yes! During the past month Connections has been tested against the beta and release candidate versions and no compatibility issues have been discovered.</p>\n<p>Another question you might be asking yourself is whether you should update or wait to upgrade to WordPress 5.0. Our advice is to wait. There are already at least two planned updates which will follow fairly quickly: 5.0.1 and 5.0.2. These updates deal with known issues that exist in 5.0. We suggest waiting for those two updates, at least, to be released before updating.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-0/">WordPress 5.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/rZjqCMwYa1M" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-0/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"https://connections-pro.com/wordpress-5-0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:64:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"QuickTip: Custom Field – Add a Checkbox Group";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/U4mdXszD7no/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox-group/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 27 Mar 2016 22:41:00 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"QuickTip";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"http://connections-pro.com/?p=370717";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:566:"<p>This is the third post in a series on how to add a checkbox group custom field to Connections. You should review these posts on how to add a custom text field and how to add a checkbox custom field before this one as this post will build upon them. I&#8217;m sure you&#8217;ll notice much of this is the ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox-group/">QuickTip: Custom Field – Add a Checkbox Group</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7405:"<p>This is the third post in a series on how to add a checkbox group custom field to Connections. You should review these posts on <a href="/quicktip-custom-field-adding-a-text-field/">how to add a custom text field</a> and <a href="/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/">how to add a checkbox custom field</a> before this one as this post will build upon them. I&#8217;m sure you&#8217;ll notice much of this is the same as the previous two tutorials, just tweaked to reflect the settings required to render a checkbox group and how to display it.</p>\n<p>Before moving on, the first thing you should do is install the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/">Code Snippets plugin</a>. After you install the Code Snippets plugin add a new snippet with the following code:</p>\n<pre lang="php" escaped="true">// Register the metabox and fields.\nadd_action( ''cn_metabox'', ''cn_register_custom_metabox_and_checkboxgroup_field'' );\n\nfunction cn_register_custom_metabox_and_checkboxgroup_field() {\n	\n    $atts = array(\n        ''title''    =&gt; ''Metabox Name'', // Change this to a name which applies to your project.\n        ''id''       =&gt; ''custom_three'', // Change this so it is unique to you project.\n        ''context''  =&gt; ''normal'',\n        ''priority'' =&gt; ''core'',\n        ''fields''   =&gt; array(\n            array(\n                ''name''       =&gt; ''Field Name'',     // Change this field name to something which applies to you project.\n                ''show_label'' =&gt; TRUE,             // Whether or not to display the ''name''. Changing it to false will suppress the name.\n                ''id''         =&gt; ''field_id_three'', // Change this so it is unique to you project. Each field id MUST be unique.\n                ''type''       =&gt; ''checkboxgroup'',  // This is the field type being added.\n                ''options''    =&gt; array(\n                    ''one''   =&gt; ''One'',\n                    ''two''   =&gt; ''Two'',\n                    ''three'' =&gt; ''Three'',\n                    ''four''  =&gt; ''Four'',\n                    ''five''  =&gt; ''Fix'',\n                    ''six''   =&gt; ''Six'',\n                ),\n                ''default''    =&gt; ''three'', // This is the default selected option. Leave blank for none.\n            ),\n        ),\n    );\n\n    cnMetaboxAPI::add( $atts );\n}\n</pre>\n<p>The above bit of code will register a new metabox with a checkbox field. This new field will now display when you add/edit your entries. It will also be displayed in the <a href="/add-on/form/">Form extension</a> and on the <a href="/add-on/link/">Link extension</a> admin profile page. A few things to note from the post on how to <a href="/quicktip-custom-field-adding-a-text-field/">add a custom text field</a> that are worth repeating:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You should change the function name <code>cn_register_custom_metabox_and_checkboxgroup_field</code>. Function names should always be unique. If you do not make sure of this, you will crash your site. (If you do crash your site, the Code Snippets plugin has a safe mode which can be enabled so you can fix it. Read the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/faq/">Code Snippets FAQ on how to enable safe mode</a> if you need to.)</li>\n<li>You need to change the metabox <code>id</code> from <code>custom_three</code>.</li>\n<li>Lastly you need to change the field <code>id</code> from <code>field_id_three</code>.</li>\n<li>When creating the new <code>id</code> names. The names should be in all lowercase and underscores should be used for spaces.</li>\n<li>Lastly, but not necessary, you should change the metabox <code>title</code> and the field <code>name</code> to something that is applicable to your project.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That’s all it takes to add a field but there is more to do to display the field. There are two ways in which you can do this. One is to register a content block that outputs the data entered in the custom field. The other is to add a few lines to a template to display it. I’ll go over the latter since that is a bit simpler to implement.</p>\n<p><div class="iconbox padding-left-30 iconbox_small iconbox_inline"><span class="iconbox_icon"><i class="icon-info-circle" style="color:#000000"></i></span><div class="iconbox_content"><h4 class="iconbox-title">Tip</h4><div class="iconbox_desc">The custom metabox is automagically compatible with both the Form and Link extensions. The metabox will automatically display on the Link admin user profile page and be immediately available to use. To have the metabox show up in Form, you must first turn it on. To do this, navigate to the Connections : Settings admin page and click the Form tab. In the Fieldset section you should see your new custom metabox as an option. Add a check to the box, drag it into the position that you wish to have it displayed and then click the Save Changes button.</div></div></div></p>\n<p>Before moving on, you should go and read how to <a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/06/04/quicktip-custom-template-override-files/">create custom template override files</a> as you really should not edit the actual template file because any changes to those files will be lost when WordPress updates the plugin. That said, displaying the field in a template requires you to open the template’s <code>card.php</code> file. The exact path to the file will depend on the template you are going to display the field. The <a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/06/04/quicktip-custom-template-override-files/">custom template override QuickTip</a> give an example on how to find this file. To keep this brief as possible I am not going to go over that here.</p>\n<p>Displaying a checkbox group in the template is a bit different because you must iterate thru each option in the checkbox group to determine if it was selected or not before displaying the option. Open the <code>card.php</code> of the template of your choice and add the following code to where you want the custom field data to display:</p>\n<pre lang="php" escaped="true">$group = $entry-&gt;getMeta(\n    array(\n        ''key'' =&gt; ''field_id_three'', // This should match exactly the field id used when registering the custom field.\n        ''single'' =&gt; TRUE           // Do not change this.\n    )\n);\n\nif ( ! empty( $group ) ) {\n\n    echo ''&lt;ul&gt;'';\n\n    foreach ( $group as $option ) {\n\n        printf( ''&lt;li&gt;%1$s&lt;/li&gt;'', esc_html( $option ) );\n    }\n\n    echo ''&lt;/ul&gt;'';\n}\n</pre>\n<p>Related QuickTips:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/quicktip-custom-field-adding-a-text-field/">Custom Field – Add a Text Field</a></li>\n<li><a href="/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/">Custom Field – Add a Checkbox</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/05/13/quicktip-tweaking-core-templates/">Tweaking Core Templates</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/06/04/quicktip-custom-template-override-files/">Custom Template Override Files</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://connections-pro.com/2015/03/19/quicktip-csv-import-custom-meta-fields/">CSV Import Custom Meta Fields</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox-group/">QuickTip: Custom Field – Add a Checkbox Group</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/U4mdXszD7no" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox-group/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox-group/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:64:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:41:"QuickTip: Custom Field – Add a Checkbox";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/FQkDDxn5bJ8/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Sun, 27 Mar 2016 21:53:24 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"QuickTip";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"http://connections-pro.com/?p=370539";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:528:"<p>This is the second post in a series on how to add a checkbox custom field to Connections. You should read the first post on how to add a custom text field before this one as this post will build upon it. Before moving on, the first thing you should do is install the Code Snippets ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/">QuickTip: Custom Field – Add a Checkbox</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6442:"<p>This is the second post in a series on how to add a checkbox custom field to Connections. You should read the first post on <a href="/quicktip-custom-field-adding-a-text-field/">how to add a custom text field</a> before this one as this post will build upon it. Before moving on, the first thing you should do is install the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/">Code Snippets plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>After you install the Code Snippets plugin add a new snippet with the following code:</p>\n<pre lang="php" escaped="true">// Register the metabox and fields.\nadd_action( ''cn_metabox'', ''cn_register_custom_metabox_and_checkbox_field'' );\n\nfunction cn_register_custom_metabox_and_checkbox_field() {\n	\n	$atts = array(\n		''title''    =&gt; ''Metabox Name'', // Change this to a name which applies to your project.\n		''id''       =&gt; ''custom_two'',   // Change this so it is unique to you project.\n		''context''  =&gt; ''normal'',\n		''priority'' =&gt; ''core'',\n		''fields''   =&gt; array(\n			array(\n				''name''       =&gt; ''Field Name'',   // Change this field name to something which applies to you project.\n				''show_label'' =&gt; TRUE,           // Whether or not to display the ''name''. Changing it to false will suppress the name.\n				''id''         =&gt; ''field_id_two'', // Change this so it is unique to you project. Each field id MUST be unique.\n				''type''       =&gt; ''checkbox'',     // This is the field type being added.\n			),\n		),\n	);\n\n	cnMetaboxAPI::add( $atts );\n}\n</pre>\n<p>The above bit of code will register a new metabox with a checkbox field. This new field will now display when you add/edit your entries. It will also be displayed in the <a href="/add-on/form/">Form extension</a> and on the <a href="/add-on/link/">Link extension</a> admin profile page. A few things to note from the post on how to <a href="/quicktip-custom-field-adding-a-text-field/">add a custom text field</a> are worth repeating:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You should change the function name from <code>cn_register_custom_metabox_and_checkbox_field</code> to something that applies to the project.  Function names should always be unique. If you do not make sure of this, you will crash your site. (If you do crash your site, the Code Snippets plugin has a safe mode which can be enabled so you can fix it. Read the <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/faq/">Code Snippets FAQ on how to enable safe mode</a> if you need to.)</li>\n<li>You need to change the metabox <code>id</code> from <code>custom_two</code>.</li>\n<li>Lastly you need to change the field <code>id</code> from <code>field_id_two</code>.</li>\n<li>When creating the new <code>id</code> names. The names should be in all lowercase and underscores should be used for spaces.</li>\n<li>Lastly, but not necessary, you should change the metabox <code>title</code> and the field <code>name</code> to something that is applicable to your project.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>That’s all it takes to add a field but there is more to do to display the field. There are two ways in which you can do this. One is to register a content block that outputs the data entered in the custom field. The other is to add a few lines to a template to display it. I’ll go over the latter since that is a bit simpler to implement.</p>\n<p><div class="iconbox padding-left-30 iconbox_small iconbox_inline"><span class="iconbox_icon"><i class="icon-info-circle" style="color:#000000"></i></span><div class="iconbox_content"><h4 class="iconbox-title">Tip</h4><div class="iconbox_desc">The custom metabox is automagically compatible with both the Form and Link extensions. The metabox will automatically display on the Link admin user profile page and be immediately available to use. To have the metabox show up in Form, you must first turn it on. To do this, navigate to the Connections : Settings admin page and click the Form tab. In the Fieldset section you should see your new custom metabox as an option. Add a check to the box, drag it into the position that you wish to have it displayed and then click the Save Changes button.</div></div></div></p>\n<p>Before moving on, you should read how to <a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/06/04/quicktip-custom-template-override-files/">create custom template override files</a> as you really should not edit the actual template file because any changes to those files will be lost when WordPress updates the plugin. That said, displaying the field in a template requires you to open the template’s <code>card.php</code> file. The exact path to the file will depend on the template you are going to display the field. The <a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/06/04/quicktip-custom-template-override-files/">custom template override QuickTip</a> gives an example on how to find this file. To keep this brief as possible I am not going to go over that here.</p>\n<p>Displaying a checkbox in the template is a bit different because the checkbox is saved as either <code>1</code> (checked) or <code>0</code> (not checked). Open the <code>card.php</code> of the template of your choice and add the following code to where you want the custom field data to display:</p>\n<pre lang="php" escaped="true">$checked = $entry-&gt;getMeta(\n        array(\n            ''key''    =&gt; ''field_id_two'', // This should match exactly the field id used when registering the custom field.\n            ''single'' =&gt; TRUE        // Do not change this.\n        )\n    );\n\nif ( $checked ) echo ''Checkbox was checked.'';\n</pre>\n<p>Related QuickTips:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/quicktip-custom-field-adding-a-text-field/">Custom Field – Add a Text Field</a></li>\n<li><a href="/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox-group/">Custom Field – Add a Checkbox Group</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/05/13/quicktip-tweaking-core-templates/">Tweaking Core Templates</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://connections-pro.com/2014/06/04/quicktip-custom-template-override-files/">Custom Template Override Files</a></li>\n<li><a href="http://connections-pro.com/2015/03/19/quicktip-csv-import-custom-meta-fields/">CSV Import Custom Meta Fields</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/">QuickTip: Custom Field – Add a Checkbox</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/FQkDDxn5bJ8" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:64:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-custom-field-checkbox/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:70:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:29:"Update Announcement: Link 3.0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/oHbXFU4Il8o/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-3-0/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Thu, 03 Mar 2016 01:34:37 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Announcement";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Development Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Pro Module";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"http://connections-pro.com/?p=367602";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:548:"<p>Link 3.0 has been release today with these new features: It is easier than ever to add the View/Add and Edit Entry links where ever you want them by using the two new shortcodes. Seamless integration with the Login extension. When using Link and Login together, Link will add additional photo and logo image options ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-3-0/">Update Announcement: Link 3.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1618:"<p><a href="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/screenshot-login-widget-link-settings.png"><img width="292" height="108" alt="" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367608_screenshot-login-widget-link-settings-292x108.png" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367608_screenshot-login-widget-link-settings-292x108@2x.png 2x"  /></a></p>\n<p>Link 3.0 has been release today with these new features:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It is easier than ever to add the View/Add and Edit Entry links where ever you want them by using the <a href="/documentation/link/#Shortcodes">two new shortcodes</a>.</li>\n<li>Seamless integration with the <a href="/add-on/login/">Login extension</a>. When using Link and Login together, Link will add additional photo and logo image options to the widget. When a linked user logs in that user&#8217;s entry logo or photo will be displayed if chosen in the widget settings. Link will also add the option to display the View/Add and Edit Entry links right in the widget so users can have easy access to viewing and editing their entry.</li>\n<li>You can even <a href="/faqs/can-i-add-the-viewadd-and-edit-links-to-my-menu/">add the View/Add and Edit Entry links to the WordPress menus</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-3-0/">Update Announcement: Link 3.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/oHbXFU4Il8o" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:62:"https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-3-0/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:57:"https://connections-pro.com/update-announcement-link-3-0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:70:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:30:"Update Announcement: Login 2.0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/2qtxhgSU1eE/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:46:"https://connections-pro.com/login-2-0/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 02 Mar 2016 18:28:54 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:12:"Announcement";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"Development Update";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:10:"Pro Module";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"http://connections-pro.com/?p=367049";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:540:"<p>The Login extension was born from many requests for providing a solution to allow the user to login to their user account. One was not provided initially because there are so many great free plugins which already offer this feature for WordPress sites. And so the Login extension was born. The feature set of Login was very ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/login-2-0/">Update Announcement: Login 2.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4302:"<p>The <a href="/add-on/login/">Login extension</a> was born from many requests for providing a solution to allow the user to login to their user account. One was not provided initially because there are so many great free plugins which already offer this feature for WordPress sites. And so the <a href="/add-on/login/">Login extension</a> was born. The feature set of Login was very basic. It provided a login widget which would only display on the entry profile detail/profile view, a login <a href="/documentation/settings/#Content_Blocks">content block</a> and shortcode which could be used in the <a href="/documentation/settings/#Require_Login">require login message</a> and that was it. This was intentional as I wanted it to be simple and easy to use. That said, it was often requested, if not expressed in these exact words, that you wanted a more full featured widget and shortcode and that is exactly what Login 2.0 is bringing to you.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an overview of the features:</p>\n<p><a href="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/screenshot-widget-common-settings.png"><img width="292" height="45" alt="" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367401_screenshot-widget-common-settings-292x45.png" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367401_screenshot-widget-common-settings-292x45@2x.png 2x"  /></a></p>\n<p>The widget is no longer limited to just the entry profile/detail view, though there is an option to enable it.</p>\n<p><div class="clearboth"></div></p>\n<p>There are separate configuration options for the widget for when the user is logged in and logged out.</p>\n<p><a href="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/screenshot-widget-logged-out-settings.png"><img width="292" height="196" alt="" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367403_screenshot-widget-logged-out-settings-292x196.png" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367403_screenshot-widget-logged-out-settings-292x196@2x.png 2x"  /></a></p>\n<p>When the user is logged out you have the option to display, or not, the &#8220;Remember me&#8221; checkbox and the &#8220;Lost Password&#8221; link. And, if you have the &#8220;Anyone can register&#8221; option enabled in the WordPress settings you have the option to display the &#8220;Register&#8221; link.</p>\n<p><div class="clearboth"></div></p>\n<p><a href="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/screenshot-widget-logged-on-settings.png"><img width="292" height="236" alt="" src="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367402_screenshot-widget-logged-on-settings-292x236.png" srcset="https://connections-pro.com/wp-content/uploads/strikingr/images/367402_screenshot-widget-logged-on-settings-292x236@2x.png 2x"  /></a></p>\n<p>The fun new options are for when the user is logged in. The widget title can be customized with their user name or first and last name. You can optionally choose to display the user&#8217;s Gravatar and even add your own custom links.</p>\n<p>Login also has basic support for both <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/bbpress/">bbPress</a> and <a href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/buddypress/">BuddyPress</a>. If one or both of those plugins are installed and active on your site, you&#8217;ll be able to add custom links to their user profile pages.</p>\n<p>And lastly, there have been a ton of actions and filters that other plugins can hook into to add additional options and features. The first plugin to take advantage that will be the <a href="/add-on/link/">Link extension</a>. The next major update to Link, which was developed in tandem with Login, features the ability to easily add the &#8220;View My Directory Entry&#8221; link, the &#8220;Edit My Directory Entry&#8221; link and added support for displaying the entry logo or photo.</p>\n<p>All in all, this is a major update which I hope you find useful!</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/login-2-0/">Update Announcement: Login 2.0</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/2qtxhgSU1eE" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:43:"https://connections-pro.com/login-2-0/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:38:"https://connections-pro.com/login-2-0/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:64:"\n		\n		\n				\n				\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n				\n								\n							\n		\n							";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:6:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:72:"QuickTip: Show the Awaiting Moderation Widget on the WordPress Dashboard";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:67:"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~3/UA3PAquxdeY/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:108:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-show-the-awaiting-moderation-widget-on-the-wordpress-dashboard/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Tue, 05 Jan 2016 18:15:14 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Connections";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"QuickTip";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:36:"http://connections-pro.com/?p=359995";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:623:"<p>I had a great question asked in the support forums today and I thought the answer to it would make for a good how-to post. I was asked how to add the Awaiting Moderation widget found on the Connections Dashboard admin to to the core WordPress Dashboard admin page. This is actually pretty easy, requiring ...</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-show-the-awaiting-moderation-widget-on-the-wordpress-dashboard/">QuickTip: Show the Awaiting Moderation Widget on the WordPress Dashboard</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Steven Zahm";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:2235:"<p>I had a great <a href="/support/topic/adding-a-to-be-moderated-dashboard-to-wp-core-dashboard/">question asked in the support forums</a> today and I thought the answer to it would make for a good how-to post. I was asked how to add the Awaiting Moderation widget found on the <a href="/documentation/dashboard/">Connections Dashboard</a> admin to to the core <a href="https://en.support.wordpress.com/dashboard/">WordPress Dashboard</a> admin page. This is actually pretty easy, requiring only a few lines of code.</p>\n<p>First, you must install the <a title="Code Snippets WordPress Plugin" href="https://wordpress.org/plugins/code-snippets/" target="_blank">Code Snippets plugin</a>. This plugin is a fantastic tool that can be used to add update safe WordPress actions and filters. When searching how-tos on the web you will very often come across a tutorial that says something like add this to your theme functions.php file. You are far better served by using this plugin instead as it makes managing these code snippets far easier and you are much less likely to break your site.</p>\n<p>After you have installed the Code Snippets plugin, add a new snippet with the following code:</p>\n<pre lang="php">function register_cn_awaiting_moderation_dashboard_widget() {\n $args = array(\n ''order_by'' => ''date_added|SORT_ASC'',\n ''template'' => ''dashboard-recent-added'',\n ''limit''    => 10,\n ''status''   => ''pending'',\n );\n \n add_meta_box( ''cn-moderate'', ''Awaiting Moderation'', array( ''cnDashboardMetabox'', ''recent'' ), ''dashboard'', ''normal'', ''default'', $args );\n}\nadd_action( ''wp_dashboard_setup'', ''register_cn_awaiting_moderation_dashboard_widget'' );</pre>\n<p><strong>Save and activate this new snippet.</strong></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s it. Now the Awaiting Moderation widget should show on the WordPress Dashboard admin page.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-show-the-awaiting-moderation-widget-on-the-wordpress-dashboard/">QuickTip: Show the Awaiting Moderation Widget on the WordPress Dashboard</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://connections-pro.com">Connections</a>.</p>\n<img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/connections-pro/news/~4/UA3PAquxdeY" height="1" width="1" alt=""/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:105:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-show-the-awaiting-moderation-widget-on-the-wordpress-dashboard/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:42:"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:100:"https://connections-pro.com/quicktip-show-the-awaiting-moderation-widget-on-the-wordpress-dashboard/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}}}s:44:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/";a:2:{s:12:"updatePeriod";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"\n	hourly	";s:7:"attribs